Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has 8 blocks in total
- It consists of 3 layers
- Bottom layer: has 3 blocks (2 yellow cubes on sides and 1 red tunnel block in center)
- Middle layer: has 3 blocks (1 blue cube, 1 green cube, 1 orange triangular roof piece)
- Top layer: has 2 orange triangular roof pieces forming a peak

Required blocks from dictionary and assembly order:

{
Step1: Move block with index 9 (yellow cube for bottom left)
Step2: Move block with index 2 (red tunnel piece for bottom center)
Step3: Move block with index 9 (yellow cube for bottom right)
Step4: Move block with index 6 (blue cube for middle right)
Step5: Move block with index 7 (green cube for middle left)
Step6: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular piece for middle right)
Step7: Move block with index 12 (orange triangular piece for top left)
Step8: Move block with index 12 (orange triangular piece for top right)
}

This assembly sequence builds the structure from bottom to top, ensuring stability. Each block is selected to match the exact orientation shown in both the target image and the block dictionary. The tunnel piece creates the central opening, while the triangular pieces form the roof structure.
